Sentencas: In solid oxide device operation, delamination and cracking cause more catastrophic damage to cell life than other degradation mechanisms, leading to more rapid cell failure.
Titulo: Multiphysics modeling of SOFC performance degradation caused by interface delamination and active layer cracking

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance degradation caused by electrode/electrolyte interface delamination and active layer cracking were investigated through in-house developed three-dimensional multiphysics simulations.
Titulo: Multiphysics modeling of SOFC performance degradation caused by interface delamination and active layer cracking

Sentencas: The multiphysics simulations, fully cali-brated against experimental datasets for button cells in a previous study, were extended to quantitatively investigate the effects of electrode/electrolyte interface delamination and active layer cracking.
Titulo: Multiphysics modeling of SOFC performance degradation caused by interface delamination and active layer cracking

Sentencas: The simulated polarization curves and impedance behavior with various levels of delamination and cracking provided insights of the performance degra-dation.
Titulo: Multiphysics modeling of SOFC performance degradation caused by interface delamination and active layer cracking

Sentencas: Furthermore, the local current distributions within the cell were analyzed for three different operating modes: constant voltage, constant current, and constant power.
Titulo: Multiphysics modeling of SOFC performance degradation caused by interface delamination and active layer cracking
